Netvision Approaching Its Biggest Gain in Two Years After Cellcom Proposal

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-03-14T10:18:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/netvision-set-for-biggest-gain-in-2-years-after-cellcom-proposal.html
  Netvision Ltd. (NTSN)  was poised for the
biggest increase in more than two years after  Cellcom Israel
Ltd. (CEL) , the country’s largest mobile-phone company, proposed a
cash purchase of the Internet-service provider.  Netvision shares surged 8.7 percent, to 46.90 shekels at
12:06 p.m. in  Tel Aviv , headed for the biggest one-day gain
since January 2009. Cellcom shares climbed 1.6 percent to 111.20
shekels.  Under the proposal, Cellcom would buy all of Netvision’s
share capital outstanding based on an estimated value of 1.5
billion shekels ($422 million), subject to adjustment, Cellcom
said today in a PRNewswire statement  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in Tel Aviv at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
